<div class="col-md-12 radio">
  <h1>The following questions are about data protection and privacy.</h1>
  <strong>
    D.1: Search for and identify personal data
  </strong>
  <p>Can the organization generally identify all locations where personal data is stored across the enterprise, including on internal servers or cloud storage, as well as those hosted by any third-party providers?</p>
  <form>
    <div class="col-md-12 radio">
     <label><input type="radio" name="optradio">Yes, the organization can fully identify all locations.</label>
   </div>
   <div class="col-md-12 radio">
     <label><input type="radio" name="optradio">Yes, but solely on internal servers or cloud storage, not on third-party hosted providers.</label>
   </div>
   <div class="col-md-12 radio">
     <label><input type="radio" name="optradio">No, neither on internal servers or cloud storage, nor on third party hosted providers.</label>
   </div>
 </form>
</div>


<div class="col-md-12">
<em> Does the organization have:</em>
</div>


<div class="col-md-12 radio">
  <p> 1. The ability to locate all instances of personal data pertaining to a given data subject?</p>
  <form>
    <div class="col-md-12 radio">
     <label><input type="radio" name="optradio">Yes, the organization has the ability to locate all these instances.</label>
   </div>
   <div class="col-md-12 radio">
     <label><input type="radio" name="optradio">No, the organization has the ability to locate these instances, but not specifically on a given data subject.</label>
   </div>
   <div class="col-md-12 radio">
     <label><input type="radio" name="optradio">No, the organization does not have the ability to locate these instances.</label>
   </div>
 </form>
</div>


<div class="col-md-12 radio">
  <p>2. A formal process in place to search for personal data in a consistent and timely manner?</p>
  <form>
    <div class="col-md-12 radio">
     <label><input type="radio" name="optradio">Yes, the organization has a formal process in place, which is also consistent in a timely manner.</label>
   </div>
   <div class="col-md-12 radio">
     <label><input type="radio" name="optradio">No, the organization has a formal process but it is not consistent in a timely manner.</label>
   </div>
   <div class="col-md-12 radio">
     <label><input type="radio" name="optradio">No, the organization does not have a formal process in place.</label>
   </div>
 </form>
</div>

<div class="col-md-12 radio">

  <p>3. Technology in place for personnel to use a single search to return all instances of personal data for a given data subject?</p>
  <form>
